1. go to https://www.bv-brc.org/ and serach "human respiratory syncytial virus A"
2.  Select Genome with numbers
3. Go to FILTER and select 

    Public -TRUE
    genome status - COMPLETE
    collection year : as required
    isolation country -USA

and click on APPLY

4. select all genome and click and hold on GENOME in right hand side and go to the FEATURE
5. search for CDS
6. click on ADV search, select GENE and type the name of GENE OF INTEREST
7. click on DOWNLOAD to download the table
8. create a bed file with  "Accession	Start	End"
9. use fetch_sequences.sh to get the sequence form NCBI
